title: FatouLemma

; Theorem
Let $$f_1,f_2,\ldots$$ be non-negative measurable function on [[measure space|MeasureSpace]] $$(S,\Sigma,\mu)$$. Then
$$
\int_S \liminf_{n\to\infty} f_n(s) d\mu \le \liminf_{n\to\infty} \int_S  f_n(s) d\mu
$$
and
$$
\int_S \limsup_{n\to\infty} f_n(s) d\mu \ge \limsup_{n\to\infty} \int_S  f_n(s) d\mu
$$